
ActionArgs is a Ruby on Rails plugin for wrangling your Controller actions' parameters.

N.B. This code set is INCOMPLETE.  It's missing one ActionController mixin.

Notes on implementation...

ActionArgs Class Hierarchy

== EXCEPTIONS ==

::StandardError (core Ruby)
   \_ ArgumentError
   \_ ConfigError


== CONFIG ==

HashCfg  (for #args_for)
 \_ OptHashCfg  (for #opt_hash)
 \_ ReqHashCfg  (for #req_hash)

ArgCfg
 \_ OptArgCfg  (for #opt)
 \_ ReqArgCfg  (for #req)


== ACCESS ==

Accessor  (for #args_for, #req_hash)
 \_ OptAccessor     (for #opt_hash)

Arg
 \_ OptArg  (for #opt)
 \_ ReqArg  (for #req)


--------

In Controller plugin:
  #args_for    : creates a HashCfg
  #access_args : creates corresponding Accessor
